    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Standard Pale Maw cultists who form the bulk of their fighting force. They wear grey robes over leather armor, bearing entropy symbols on their chests. They fight with the reckless courage of absolute faith, not self-preservation.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>ABILITIES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Cultist's Blade</strong> (Main, Melee, Might): T1 2 dmg; T2 4 dmg; T3 6 dmg.</li><li><strong>Entropy Chant</strong> (Maneuver, 1M, Area 20ft): PM allies in area gain +1 to next attack. Enemies in area: Presence test or frightened EoNT.</li></ul><p><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Pack Mentality:</strong> +1 to attack rolls when an adjacent PM ally is also engaged with the same target.</li><li><strong>Fanatic's Resolve:</strong> When reduced to 0 SP, may make one final free strike before falling.</li></ul><p><strong>TACTICS:</strong> Work in groups. Use Pack Mentality to overwhelm single targets. Entropy Chant before engaging. Prioritize getting adjacent to Kaelen.</p><p><strong>BEAT 16 USE:</strong> Serve as the mass of Pale Maw forces at Beinvaka (20–30 present). In combat, they rush forward while Veterans hold flanks and the Inquisitor directs.</p>",
